						---FeedForwardNN_With_NumPy---
Recuirments:
	Python 3
	Numpy
	Matplotlib
	Pandas
Optional: Use Anaconda envirment with Spyder IDE

SetUp:
0)Download the Git files and put them inside a new folder, that will be your working directory

1)Go to this website:
	http://yann.lecun.com/exdb/mnist/
and download these files:
	train-images-idx3-ubyte.gz:  training set images (9912422 bytes) 
	train-labels-idx1-ubyte.gz:  training set labels (28881 bytes) 

Extract them into your working directory, which is the folder that contains the .py files

In your working directory:
Create a folder named x_train and put inside the extracted train-images.idx3-ubyte
Create a folder named y_train and put inside the extracted train-labels.idx3-ubyte

!Make sure the form of the extracted files is .idx3-ubyte and not -idx3-ubyte

2)Install mlxtend with:
pip install mlxtend

3)Run load_mnist.py

4)The created folders now contain csv files of MNIST!
